    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-05-17T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-05-17T18:00:00-05:00" n="387"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d387">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.83241/80: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hare</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-05-17T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 17, 1940—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>34. Your 63, May 8, 4 p.m. You are authorized to reply to the Egyptian Government
                    in the sense of the Department’s instruction no. 75 of March 12, 1935.<note
                        n="55" xml:id="d387fn55">Not printed.</note> You should state that in as
                    much as this Government does not limit the number of Egyptian diplomatic and
                    consular officers to whom immunities are granted in this country, it is assumed
                    that the immunities which the Egyptian Government proposes <pb facs="0529"
                        n="517" xml:id="pg_517"/> to extend to American Foreign Service Officers in
                    accordance with international law and usage on the basis of reciprocity will
                    likewise be without any numerical limitation. Your reply should also, in making
                    reference to the draft consular convention which was transmitted to the Egyptian
                    Government for negotiation on October 21, 1939,<note n="56" xml:id="d387fn56"
                        >See despatch No. 1899, October 21, 1939, from the Minister in Egypt, <ref
                            target="frus1939v04#pg_486">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1939, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">iv</hi>, p. 486</ref>.</note> inquire as to the
                    views of the Egyptian Government concerning that draft.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
